</note>
<note id="fs-id1313207" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1280620">
<problem id="fs-id1364520">
<para id="fs-id1363841">Plot each point on the same rectangular coordinate system: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1448060"><para id="fs-id1171105196606"><newline/>
<media id="fs-id1437436" alt="This answer graph shows the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y-axis each run from -6 to 6. There are two labeled points: the first is ordered pair (2, 4), and the second is (4, 2)">
