<para id="eip-707">How do the signs affect the location of the points?</para><example id="fs-id1280334">
<exercise id="fs-id1280072">
<problem id="fs-id1279622">
<para id="fs-id1237862">Plot each point: <list id="eip-id1164753132679" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="circled"><item><span class="token">ⓐ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>−5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></item><item><span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>−5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></item><item><span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></item><item><span class="token">ⓓ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−2</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:math></item></list></para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1315559">
<title>Solution</title>
<para id="fs-id1294549">As we locate the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext>-coordinate</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> and the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mtext>-coordinate</m:mtext><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> we must be careful with the signs.<newline/>
<media id="fs-id1317266" alt="The graph shows the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y-axis each run from -7 to 7. The point “ordered pair 5, 2” is labeled “ordered pair 5, 2”. The point “ordered pair -5, 2” is labeled “ordered pair -5, 2”. The point “ordered pair -5, -2” is labeled “ordered pair -5, -2”. The point “ordered pair 5, -2” is labeled “ordered pair 5, -2”.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_11_01_028_img.jpg"/>
</media></para>
</solution>
