<example id="fs-id1340490"><exercise id="fs-id1444543"><problem id="fs-id1444546">
<para id="fs-id1444548">Determine which ordered pairs are solutions of the equation. <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>:</m:mtext></m:math><list id="eip-id1166567425683" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="circled"><item><span class="token">ⓐ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></item><item><span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></item><item><span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>−2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−7</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:math></item></list></para></problem>
