</para><table id="fs-id1569134" class="unnumbered" summary="This table has 5 rows and 3 columns. The first row is the equation y = 5 x - 1. The next row is a header row and it labels each column “x”, “y”, and  “ordered pair x, y”. Under the column “x” are the values  0, 1, and 2. Under the column “y” are the values 1, -4, and 9. Under the column “ordered pair x, y” are the values “ordered pair  0, -1”, “ordered pair 1, 4”, and “ordered pair 2, 9”."><label/>
