<row>
<entry>Write the ordered pair.</entry>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></entry>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></entry>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math></entry>
</row>
</tbody>



</tgroup>
</table><para id="fs-id1426302">So <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>20</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> are three solutions to the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<table id="fs-id1580614" class="unnumbered" summary="This table it titled x - 4 y =8. It has 4 rows and 3 columns. The first row is a header row and it labels each column “x”, “y”, and  “ordered pair x, y”. Under the column “x” are the values 0, 8, and 20. Under the column “y” are the values  -2, 0, and 3. Under the column “ordered pair x, y” are the values “ordered pair  0,  -2”, “ordered pair 8, 0”, and “ordered pair 20, 3”."><label/>
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
<colspec colnum="3" colname="c3"/>
<thead><row valign="top">
<entry align="center" namest="c1" nameend="c3"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>

<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>20</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table><para id="fs-id1570150">Remember, there are an infinite number of solutions to each linear equation. Any point you find is a solution if it makes the equation true.</para>
</solution>
</exercise></example>
