</item><item><emphasis>Coordinates of Zero</emphasis><list id="eip-id1170325448704"><item>Points with a <emphasis effect="italics">y-</emphasis>coordinate equal to 0 are on the <emphasis effect="italics">x-</emphasis>axis, and have coordinates ( <emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis>, 0).</item>
<item>Points with a <emphasis effect="italics">x-</emphasis>coordinate equal to 0 are on the <emphasis effect="italics">y-</emphasis>axis, and have coordinates ( 0, <emphasis effect="italics">b</emphasis>).</item>
<item>The point (0, 0) is called the origin. It is the point where the <emphasis effect="italics">x-</emphasis>axis and <emphasis effect="italics">y-</emphasis>axis intersect.</item></list></item></list></section>
